    • listItems

      public String listItems()
      This method builds invalid input: '&' returns a string that contains all items in the arrayList. For each item store in the array lists the listItems will show the index that is associated. If there is no items in the arrayList it will return "No items added".
      Returns:
      A string which is built up to includes all the products in the arrayList or "No items added" is returned.

    • numberOfCompleteItems

      public int numberOfCompleteItems()
      This method look at the compleation status for each in the arrayList
      Returns:
      If their is no items in the arrayList it will return true, It will use for each loop and once it find one item [todo] it return false. If all items are completed it will send back true.
